<item>
            <title>[LU-18985] TCU: DNE2 striped directory handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18985</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When files in a striped directory are deleted, each of the stub pFID objects may need to be created on multiple MDTs, so that when there is a file deleted on that MDT it will be possible to move it into the stub directory without a distributed DNE transaction.&lt;br/&gt;
When displaying such directories to the user via the .Trash/pFID directory on the client, it would be useful to present these multiple stub directories at a single virtual unified directory. That allows a user to see all of the files in the directory in a single location, even if they are stored in multiple MDTs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
